        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/7/4/174fadd07fd54c9afe288e96558c92e0c1da733a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$n$\" width=\"10\" height=\"8\" /> be a positive integer. A number <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/1/9/019e9892786e493964e145e7c5cf7b700314e53b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A$\" width=\"13\" height=\"13\" /> consists of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/9/3/f93f5c51ea4b04b4992b003b39479f29018f6bda.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2n$\" width=\"19\" height=\"12\" /> digits, each of which is 4; and a number <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/f/5/ff5fb3d775862e2123b007eb4373ff6cc1a34d4e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$B$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> consists of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/7/4/174fadd07fd54c9afe288e96558c92e0c1da733a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$n$\" width=\"10\" height=\"8\" /> digits, each of which is 8. Prove that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/3/e/33ee64d6c2e34e2cd41d2819b7a3c4ae253f485f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A+2B+4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"91\" height=\"14\" /> is a perfect square.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Using the definition of base 10, we know that\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/b/d/fbdee3331ae8e49b160eacb9b95e6ced31bb210d.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\begin{align*} A &amp;= 4(10^{2n-1} + 10^{2n-2} \\cdots 10^1 + 10^0) \\\\ &amp;= \\frac{4 \\cdot (10^{2n} - 1)}{9} \\\\ B &amp;= 8(10^{n-1} + 10^{n-2} \\cdots 10^1 + 10^0) \\\\ &amp;= \\frac{8 \\cdot (10^{n} - 1)}{9}. \\end{align*}\" width=\"285\" height=\"139\" />\nThus, we have\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/2/1/12104d06bbcdce7e967c2d5a6671d82c975624e1.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\begin{align*} A+2B+4 &amp;= \\frac{4 \\cdot 10^{2n} - 4 + 16 \\cdot 10^n - 16 + 36}{9} \\\\ &amp;= \\frac{4 \\cdot (10^n)^2 + 16 \\cdot 10^n + 16}{9} \\\\ &amp;= \\left(\\frac{2(10^n + 2)}{3}\\right)^2. \\end{align*}\" width=\"365\" height=\"137\" />\nSince we know that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/3/e/33ee64d6c2e34e2cd41d2819b7a3c4ae253f485f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A+2B+4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"91\" height=\"14\" /> is an integer, we confirm that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/3/e/33ee64d6c2e34e2cd41d2819b7a3c4ae253f485f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A+2B+4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"91\" height=\"14\" /> is a perfect square.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_Also\">See Also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See Also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%; border:1px solid black; width:80%;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#ccf;text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2003_JBMO\" title=\"2003 JBMO\">2003 JBMO</a></b> (<b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2003_JBMO_Problems\" title=\"2003 JBMO Problems\">Problems</a></b> • <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://artofproblemsolving.com/community/c13_contests\">Resources</a>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Preceded&#160;by<br /><b>First Problem</b>\n</td>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Followed&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2003 JBMO Problems/Problem 2 (page does not exist)\">Problem 2</a></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">1</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"2003 JBMO Problems/Problem 2 (page does not exist)\">2</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3\" title=\"2003 JBMO Problems/Problem 3\">3</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/2003_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"2003 JBMO Problems/Problem 4\">4</a> <b></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/JBMO_Problems_and_Solutions,_with_authors\" title=\"JBMO Problems and Solutions, with authors\"> All JBMO Problems and Solutions</a></b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907160548\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.020 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.021 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 126/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 395/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 839/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 43/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1959/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    1.988      1 Template:JBMO_box\n100.00%    1.988      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:16703-0!canonical and timestamp 20240907160548 and revision id 97432\n -->\n"
